Taint Effects
1. NoSchedule:

Meaning
Do not schedule NEW pods on this node.
Existing pods continue running.

Example
kubectl taint nodes ip-192-168-17-51.ec2.internal gpu=true:NoSchedule

2. PreferNoSchedule
Meaning
Avoid scheduling pods here if possible.

If Kubernetes has no better node,
it may still schedule the pod.

Example
kubectl taint nodes ip-192-168-17-51.ec2.internal gpu=true:PreferNoSchedule
 
3. NoExecute
Meaning
Do not schedule new pods.
Also evict (remove) existing pods
that do not tolerate this taint.

Example
kubectl taint nodes ip-192-168-17-51.ec2.internal gpu=true:NoExecute


















